# Enterprise Table Design Standards

Always use **content-weighted** columns. Never use equal-width tables.

## Column priority

**Priority 1 — Flexible** (one per table, absorbs trailing width):
Description · Customer · Remarks · Product · Long-text notes

**Priority 2 — Medium** (~110–170px, content-driven):
Dates · AWB · Reference numbers · Channel / source

**Priority 3 — Compact** (~70–115px, content-driven):
Status · Actions · Download · IDs

## Width sizing

Per column: `width = max(longest header label, longest body cell) + 24px padding` (+ `18px` right-pad for monetary columns).

If a table has no Priority-1 column, set `table { width: auto; min-width: <sum>; }` to prevent `.ord-tbl { width: 100% }` from auto-distributing leftover viewport as within-cell whitespace.

If a table has a Priority-1 column, keep `width: 100%` and let that column absorb extra space.

## Financial screens

- Group monetary columns adjacent — never split by Status / Date.
- Right-align every monetary cell **and** its header.
- Add a subtle `inset 1px 0 0 0 var(--border)` divider on the first monetary column so the group reads as one block.
- Use compact action columns (~70–86px) pinned at the extreme right.
- Apply `padding-right: 18px` to monetary columns so the right edge stays close to its header.

## Before finalizing

- [ ] Header label and body content drive width — no manual padding.
- [ ] One absorber column (Priority 1) OR `width: auto` if none.
- [ ] No equal-width distribution.
- [ ] Monetary group is visually flush + right-aligned.
- [ ] Action column is compact and pinned right.
- [ ] Table density matches **Wallet Transactions** and **Pickup Requests**.

## Concrete example

```css
/* ❌ BAD — equal-ish widths, header drives oversized ID, monetaries split */
.bad-tbl th:nth-child(1) { width: 150px; }  /* ID column 3× content */
.bad-tbl th:nth-child(2) { width: 150px; }  /* Status with empty space */
.bad-tbl th:nth-child(3) { width: 150px; }  /* Amount — split from other amounts */

/* ✅ GOOD — content-weighted, monetary group flush right */
.good-tbl { width: auto; min-width: 920px; }
.good-tbl th:nth-child(1) { width:  80px; }  /* ID#       — compact */
.good-tbl th:nth-child(2) { width: 108px; }  /* Status    — compact */
.good-tbl th:nth-child(3) { width: 150px; }  /* Date      — medium */
.good-tbl th:nth-child(4) { width: 124px; padding-right: 18px;
  box-shadow: inset 1px 0 0 0 var(--border); }  /* Amount — start of group */
.good-tbl th:nth-child(5) { width: 160px; padding-right: 18px; }  /* Amount */
.good-tbl th:nth-child(6) { width:  76px; text-align: center; }   /* Action */
```

Reference implementations: `src/features/finance/wallet/WalletTransactionsPage.tsx`, `src/features/finance/remittance/RemittancesPage.tsx`.
